This paper deals with facial image manipulation using adversarial learning, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of cycle-consistency and texture-loss, which are common techniques in generative models and deep learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the manipulation of facial landmarks, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper deals with multi-modality portrait manipulation, which involves the use of multiple modalities such as images and videos, and thus can be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM).
